In this article, President Trump makes various remarks during a press conference at the White House. He mentions his plans to speak in front of farmers in New Orleans and mentions that the Clemson championship team will be coming to the White House. He also discusses the ongoing government shutdown and the need for border security. Trump rejects the suggestion to reopen the government temporarily, stating that he wants to get the issue resolved. He denies ever working for Russia and dismisses allegations of racism. Trump also talks about his confidence in negotiations with China on trade and criticizes the FBI and intelligence agencies. He concludes by saying that he is not looking to declare a national emergency to fund the border wall.